&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate the delivery of QRT Academy programmes, events, and academic engagement activities, including workshops, seminars, competitions, and conferences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage event logistics, communications, and supporting materials to ensure successful delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain programme plans, feedback and metrics, documentation, timelines, and operational reporting across Academy activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a key operational contact for universities, academic partners, programme participants and internal stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with colleagues across the business to support the successful delivery of Academy programmes and events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the continuous improvement of operational processes supporting QRT Academy&#39;s global activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your present skillset:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree-level qualification, ideally in Business, Events Management, Education, Communications, Science, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organisational and coordination skills, with the ability to manage multiple priorities and deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
